&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Box Needs You&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This &lt;strong&gt;Engineering Business Operations Manager&lt;/strong&gt; will be a key partner for the Engineering Business Operations and Strategy (EBOS) organization, responsible for providing operational support and expertise to Box Engineering teams across the Build organization. This role will have a focus on our EMEA teams. You will guide and prepare teams through planning and reporting processes - including Annual Planning, Quarterly Planning, Quarterly Business Reviews, and monthly Operational Reviews - and drive critical processes for tracking performance metrics and helping leadership measure and report on key goals. We are looking for someone who can help us scale in a way that supports our continued growth. This position reports directly to the Senior Director of EBOS.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own optimization strategies and recognize opportunities to improve team functions; design and improve operational workflows to reduce friction and increase efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Guide and prepare Engineering teams across EMEA for all planning and reporting processes, including Annual Planning, Quarterly Planning, Quarterly Business Reviews (QBRs), monthly Operational Reviews, and related cadences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive and maintain OKR tracking and KPI measurement for engineering teams; build reporting and dashboards that give leadership clear visibility into performance and progress against goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Engineering leadership on production support and SLA management; monitor SLA performance, and support resolution and communication.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Compile and analyze data from engineering and cross-functional partners to assess performance, identify operational bottlenecks, and support strategic decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and deliver presentations and materials for leadership and business reviews; ensure consistent, accurate reporting across EBOS and Build organization stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Product, Engineering, and Finance on planning alignment, resource allocation, and operational initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support ad-hoc EBOS projects and operational improvements to enable scale and continued growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&

